# Windows batch files require CRLF line endings -- cmd.exe misparses LF-only
# .bat files under some non-interactive invocations (confirmed 2026-07-12,
# see Planning/security-control-document.md and Planning/installation-guide.md).
# This has regressed at least twice from editors/tools normalizing to LF on
# save. Force CRLF here so it can't happen again regardless of local git
# config or editor settings.
*.bat text eol=crlf

# Shell scripts must stay LF regardless of platform.
*.sh text eol=lf
